y that enable the licit life of capitalism—practices that are legally sanctioned, widely replicated, and ordinary, at the same time as they are messy, contested, and, arguably, indefensible.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aCapitalismzEquatorial Guinea. 0aOil industriesxEconomic aspectszEquatorial Guinea. 0aPetroleum industry and tradezEquatorial Guinea. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147800457840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478004578423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478004578/original  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles